My 3 Caribbean travel suggestions for 2024! What would you pick?! 🏝️ 

1. Grenada 🇬🇩 
This country is a lot more than just beaches. It’s also one of the largest producers of nutmeg in the world.

2. Dominica 🇩🇲 
What’s not to love about a country that’s called ‘The Nature Isle?!’ This island is a total gem with its own resident pod of sperm whales.

3. Belize 🇧🇿 
Ya’better Belize it! This country’s got the Blue Hole (Google that!), a beautiful selection of cayes & reefs, and also a huge population of menonite folk! 

#KiltedAdventures #caribbeanvacation #HolidayDestinations

Maybe we should call this “Burns Week!” 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿 
On the 25th January, (some) folk around the world celebrate Burns Night. “What is that?!” I hear you say! Well, it’s an annual celebration dedicated to the life and works of Robert Burns, Scotland’s National poet. He wrote some great poems, which were dedicated to plenty of things (a mouse and louse included!), but what many people don’t know is that he wrote more songs than he did poems! 🎶 
#RobertBurns #AuldLangSyne #RabbieBurns
